<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1435,1748,1862]" box="[151,881,1840,1862]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
Type species by monotypy: 
<taxonomicName authority="Herrich-Schaeffer, 1839" authorityName="Herrich-Schaeffer" authorityYear="1839" box="[434,877,1840,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Capsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coryzoides">
<emphasis box="[434,623,1840,1862]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">Capsus coryzoides</emphasis>
Herrich-Schaeffer, 1839
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1901,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413">
The genus is distinguished by the following characters: small to medium sized body; brownish back coloration, with contrasting white maculae across clavus and corium; flattened collar; a stridulatory device on inner surface of metafemora; and very long, slender endosoma, with complex sub-apical or apical region. For detailed description see 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[194,405,2009,2034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="413" refString="Schuh, R. T. (1984) Revision of the Phylinae (Hemiptera, Miridae) of the Indo-Pacific. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 177, 1 ‾ 476." type="journal article" year="1984">Schuh (1984: 117)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[323,454,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[323,454,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Hallodapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the tropics and subtropics of the Old World consisting of about 47 described species (
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[402,677,188,213]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Schuh, R. T. &amp; Menard, K. L. (2013) A revised classification of the Phylinae (Insecta: Heteroptera: Miridae): Arguments for placement of genera. American Museum Novitates, 3785, 1 ‾ 72." type="journal article" year="2013">Schuh &amp; Menard, 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Miyomoto (1966) described two species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1242,1373,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1242,1373,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Hallodapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Japan. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh" box="[230,383,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Schuh, R. T. (1984) Revision of the Phylinae (Hemiptera, Miridae) of the Indo-Pacific. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 177, 1 ‾ 476." type="journal article" year="1984">Schuh (1984)</bibRefCitation>
treated comprehensively the Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[793,924,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[793,924,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Hallodapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fauna, recognizing sixteen species. In recent studies 
<bibRefCitation author="Duwal" box="[237,454,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Duwal, R. K., Jung, S. &amp; Lee, S. (2014) Taxonomic revision of the tribe Hallodapini Van Duzee (Hemiptera: Miridae: Phylinae) from Korea. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology, 17, 601 ‾ 607." type="journal article" year="2014">
Duwal 
<emphasis box="[321,372,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">et al</emphasis>
., 2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[468,651,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Yasunaga, T. (2001) Family Miridae Hahn, plant bugs. In: Yasunaga, T., Takai, M. &amp; Kawasawa, T. (Eds.), A Field Guide to Japanese Bugs II. Zenkoku Noson Kyoiku Kyokai, Publishing Co. Ltd., Tokyo, pp. 1 ‾ 96, 111 ‾ 351. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="2001">Yasunaga, 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[664,847,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Yasunaga, T. (2012) Review of the phyline plant bug tribe Auricillocorini from Asia, with descriptions of a new genus and nine new species from Japan, Nepal and Thailand (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae). Zootaxa, 3530, 1 ‾ 24." type="journal article" year="2012">Yasunaga, 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[860,1122,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Yasunaga, T., Yamada, K. &amp; Artchawakom, T. (2013 a) Additional records of the plant bug genus Hallodapus Fieber from Thailand, with proposal of a new synonymy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae). Zootaxa, 3701 (5), 596 ‾ 599. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3701.5.5" type="journal article" year="2013" yearSuffix="a">
Yasunaga 
<emphasis box="[977,1028,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">et al</emphasis>
., 2013a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" box="[1135,1149,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Yasunaga, T., Yamada, K. &amp; Artchawakom, T. (2013 b) New or little known taxa of the plant bug tribe Hallodapini (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae: Phylinae) from Thailand, with descriptions of three new species of the genus Acrorrhinium Noualhier. Zootaxa, 3647 (3), 429 ‾ 442." type="journal article" year="2013" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Yasunaga" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" refString="Yasunaga, T. &amp; Duwal, R. K. (2015) Further records and descriptions of the plant bug subfamily Phylinae (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Miridae) from Thailand. Zootaxa, 3981 (2), 193 ‾ 219." type="journal article" year="2015">Yasunaga &amp; Duwal, 2015</bibRefCitation>
, added distribution records from different regions of Asia for several species. We herein provide new distributional records for some known species. Four 
<taxonomicName box="[766,897,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Hallodapus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="414" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[766,897,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Hallodapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are recognized for the first time from Nepal.
</paragraph>
